betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Welcome to SpaceCraft, a modpack all about spacetravel and futuristic advancements.

Before you start playing this awesome pack, you must choose a packmode. 
There are currently 6 modes:

- Rushed
- Abnormal
- Genius

- Kitchen-sink rushed
- Kitchen-sink Abnormal
- Kitchen-sink Genius

§l

*** Rushed ***
§r
Rushed will provide you with shortcuts so your playtime is drastically shorter than Abnormal mode.

§l*** Abnormal ***
§r
If you are new to modded minecraft or like a more casual gameplay this mode is for you.

§l*** Genius ***
§r
When you have played all available modpacks out there and know about the content of every mod, you can now forget about all that and experience the new mechanics in this modpack. 
This mode requires you to think outside of the box. Not only are a lot of recipes changed, machines from all mods have been integraded 

§l

*** Kitchen-sink Rushed/Abnormal/Genius ***
§r
Just the regular kitchen-sink mode. Quests are optional so no forced progression. You can choose which difficult

We need to strip the burned bark to get Oak Log
So let's strip them bitc*es!


- Take your axe in your hand
Things can get rough now!
- Hit the Charcoal Log with right click

Breathing vacuum or oxygen, which one do you prefer?
Even though I prefer breathing vacuum but my body can't handle that.
Since there isn't any other alternative get ready to make oxygen!

- Gather 18 oxygen shards

We are going to need cobblestone, probably lots of it

- Break asteroid stone to obtain pebbles
- Craft 10 cobblestone by filling all crafting slots
PS. keep a few or more than a few pebbles you'll need them later on

Gather silkworms from dirt. After you retreive or at least tried to catch a silkworm the dirt isn't fertilised anymore and changes in coarse dirt.

- Use a shovel on a normal dirt block while sneaking
- Collect at least 1 silkworm

Let's make life easier by using tools

-JEI will always be your friend

Starting a fire with pebbles and cobblestone is a bit of pain in the ass, don't you think?

- Craft a furnace

Before we're able to make a furnace, a charcoal pit has to be made.
Obtaining charcoal for the furnace crafting recipe is done by crafting log piles

- Craft a log pile (@Charcoal Pit)
- Craft 1 block of cobblestone
- Collect multiple pebbles

You can get a crafting table pretty easily
Choose which charcoallog you want to convert to a crafting table

- Make sure your hand is empty
- Now Sneak!
- Hit the log with your hand

Tadaaa your first crafting table

We need to create a charcoal pit for charcoal.

- Place down a log pile, make sure it is fully touched by non-flammable blocks but leave the top side open.

- Now you need to slab down an adjoining block of cobblestone

- In order to start a fire throw pebbles to the block of cobblestone and observe

- Once a logpile burns all adjecent log piles will also burn.


NOTE: Be sure that every side including the top is covered once the fire is lit otherwise all piles will burn up.

Choose which hammer you would like to make, wood or stone?

- Craft a wooden hammer or stone hammer

Gravel is cobblestone that has been hammered

- Hammer blocks of cobblestone
- Collect 4 gravel

Making planks is a bit unusual in this pack

- Smack down a block of planks
- Break it with a hammer

Barrels will make you dirt in the early game stages

- Craft a wooden barrel

With the ash from the charcoal pit you can make dirt

- Fill up the wooden barrel with ash which you gathered before in the quest 'Charcoal Pit'
- Let it compost
- Wait...
- Wait some more...
- Retreive your compost


- Collect 10 pieces of dirt

Silkworms compost into wool which drops a single piece of string

- Fill a wooden barrel with 10 silkworms
- Wait until it is composted
- Collect 9 wool

Boy, digging with my bare hands in space is a tough job. I wish I brought a shovel with me. Luckily there is always room to impovise.

- Craft a stone shovel

Early game items come partially from the sieves. you'll be able to gather more resources as you upgrade your mesh tier. With the basic string mesh the drops aren't all that great but know this it will get better.

- Craft a 'String Mesh'
- Place the mesh in the 'Oak Sieve'

- Collect 1 'Worm'
- Collect 1 'Seeds'
- Collect 1 'Coffee Seeds'
- Collect 4 'Copper Ore Piece'

The oxygen pad is the exact thing you need to survive in space. Slab some oxygen crystals against it and you are good to go.
Space is quite comfortable right?

- Craft a 'Oxygen Pad'
- Put 'Small Oxygen Crystal' or 'Oxygen Crystal' in the top slot of the 'Oxygen Pad'
- Stand on top of a filled 'Oxygen Pad' while your spacesuit is equipped

In order to fill your oxygen back up, copper is required for the machinery to make it all posible.

- Sieve lots 'gravel'
- Collect 'Copper Ore Pieces'
- Craft 'Copper Ore Chunks'

- Cook the 'Copper Ore Chunks' this will transform it in 'Small Copper Chunk'
- Craft a block of 'Copper Block - Purity (8%)'

The 'Small Plate Presser' Will make you some nifty items eg. plates.

- Craft a block of 'Copper Block - Purity (8%)'
- Craft a 'Small Plate Presser'
- Craft a 'Lever'

You've made the 'Small Plate Presser' however you need to go on a trip. For the presser to work you need to find a single block of obsidian. After that follow the instructions below

- Find a block of obsidian in a asteroid
- Place the 'Small Plate Presser' a block above the obsidian
- Place the block of 'Copper Block - Purity (8%)' between the obsidian and the small plate presser

- Toggle the lever and collect the copper plate
